tldr: The user requested a thorough aesthetic review and improvement for their
  sleep questionnaire app. The app underwent a comprehensive visual redesign
  with a new sleep-themed color palette, enhanced UI components, consistent
  styling across all sections, and a critical bug fix for null input values.
overview: The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetic
  appeal of their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was visually
  lacking. The process began with a comprehensive review of the existing
  styling, identifying areas such as a generic color palette, plain backgrounds,
  dense form sections, and a lack of visual personality. The approach involved
  implementing a new, calming sleep-themed color palette using OKLCH,
  redesigning the main form layout with subtle background elements and an
  enhanced progress indicator, and overhauling individual UI components like
  checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards for a more polished look. All
  questionnaire sections were updated to ensure consistent styling, replacing
  old gray boxes with new card-style groupings and themed headers. The Report
  section, initially having inconsistent hardcoded gradients, was also updated
  to align with the new sleep theme. Additionally, a critical console error
  related to  values being passed to input fields was identified and
  fixed. The outcome is a visually cohesive, professional, and calming
  application that better suits its purpose as a sleep health questionnaire.
